# Node Slack Web API SDK Installation & Usage

## Installation
```bash
npm install @slack/web-api
```

## Import & Initialize
```javascript
const { WebClient } = require('@slack/web-api');
const web = new WebClient(process.env.SLACK_TOKEN);
```

The documentation states: "You must initialize it with an access token so that you don't have to provide the token each time you call a method."

## Example API Calls

**chat.postMessage** - Send a message to a channel:
```javascript
await web.chat.postMessage({
  channel: 'C123456789',
  text: 'Hello world!'
});
```

**conversations.create** - Create a new channel:
```javascript
await web.conversations.create({
  name: 'my-channel'
});
```

**conversations.invite** - Add users to a channel:
```javascript
await web.conversations.invite({
  channel: 'C123456789',
  users: 'U123456789,U987654321'
});
```

**users.lookupByEmail** - Find user by email:
```javascript
await web.users.lookupByEmail({
  email: 'user@example.com'
});
```

**auth.test** - Verify token validity:
```javascript
await web.auth.test();
```

All methods return Promises and accept options as object properties. The documentation emphasizes this design: "For every method, you pass arguments as properties of an `options` object. This helps with the readability of your code because every argument has a name."

